  "transcript": "Here's how to make YouTube shorts that post themselves step by step. Go to nnn.io and create a new workflow. In step one, add an OpenAI node to write your short script. Step two, add a voice node with Eleven Labs to generate the voice over. Step three, add Pika Labs or Runway to turn that audio into a full video. Step four, add a YouTube node, connect your API key, and set it to upload automatically. Now every time you run it, AI writes, voices edits, and posts a brand new short. Your YouTube channel basically runs itself on autopilot. So if you want my exact workflow setup and prompts, just comment system, and I'll send them over.",
